*) there are two types of machines

    1) Control machine :− Machine from where we can manage other machines.
    2) Remote machine :− Machines which are handled/controlled by control machine.

*) Control Machine Requirements

   1) Ansible can be run from any machine with Python 2 (versions 2.6 or 2.7) (or) Python 3
     (versions 3.5 and higher) installed.
       Note :− Windows does not support control machine.
   2) By default, Ansible uses ssh to manage remote machine.


*) Ubuntu/Debian

     $ sudo apt update
     $ sudo apt install software-properties-common
     $ sudo apt-add-repository --yes --update ppa:ansible/ansible
     $ sudo apt install ansible
     $ ansible --version

*) RHEL

     $ sudo dnf install python3 python3-pip -y
     $ sudo dnf -y install https://dl.fedoraproject.org/pub/epel/epel-release-latest-8.noarch.rpm
     $ sudo dnf install  --enablerepo epel-playground  ansible
     $ ansible --version

*) CentOS

        $ yum install epel-release
        $ sudo yum install ansible
        $  ansible --version.

*) Amazon Linux

      $ yum install python
      $ yum install python-pip
      $ pip install ansible
      $ ansible --version

*) through pip

    $ pip install ansible




